==English==

===Etymology===
Shortened from [[napkin]]

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æpi|-æpi]]

===Adjective===
'''nappy'''

# Tightly curled or twisted; [[kinky]].
#:Example:  '''Nappy''' hair is relatively common among those of African descent.

===Noun===
'''nappy''' ({{plural}} [[nappies]])

# {{UK}} {{AU}} An [[absorbent]] [[garment]] worn by a [[baby]] who does not yet have [[voluntary]] control of its [[bladder]] and [[bowels]] or by someone who is [[incontinent]].

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[vaippa]]
*French: [[couche]] {{f}}
*Italian: [[pannolino]] {{m}}

====Synonyms====
*{{US}} (''Canada''): [[diaper]] 
*{{UK}} {{archaic}}: [[napkin]] 


